If you’ve ever played with Lego, chances are you’ve attempted to build a freestanding tower of bricks.

But while yours probably toppled only inches from the ground, a team of Lego constructors recently built a tower that reached a world record-breaking 114ft (34.76 metres).

It was constructed in front of Saint Stephen's Basilica in Budapest and was topped off with a Lego version of a Rubik’s Cube.

