The tower took four days to build and the record was verified at the weekend.

The mayor of the city's 5th district said he hoped the record would promote Budapest to the world, before he was lifted on a crane to the top of the tower to place the last piece.

‘This is a modern obelisk behind us and it shows that with lots of minute engineering knowledge and diligence how we can call attention to the fact that this is one of the most beautiful squares of Budapest,' Mayor Antal Rogan said.

'I hope we will be able to achieve a new world record, and if it happens we will be able to draw even more tourists to [the region].

The tower was disassembled the day after.

 

